President Obama had a call with Prime Minister Hariri of Lebanon where he expressed his support for the Lebanese people and their upcoming anniversary of the assassination of former Prime Minister Rafiq Hariri. They discussed the importance of the Special Tribunal for Lebanon in bringing the perpetrators to justice. The President also emphasized the United States' support for Lebanon's sovereignty and independence and their cooperation in bilateral issues, including support for the Lebanese Armed Forces. They also discussed the United States' commitment to UN Security Council Resolutions and their partnership on the Security Council for the next two years. President Obama expressed his desire to meet with Prime Minister Hariri.